[assistant] Fixed the native-image build failure by moving `SingleJacksonRuntimeHintsSpringFactoriesLoader` out of the public test class.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause: JUnit’s native-image feature recursively registers nested test classes/members. Because the helper was a nested class extending `SpringFactoriesLoader`, registration walked into Spring’s nested Kotlin support classes and failed on missing optional `kotlin.reflect.KCallable`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated file:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - `tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-jackson/4.0.2/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot_jackson/JacksonAutoConfigurationInnerJacksonAutoConfigurationRuntimeHintsTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] The helper is now a package-private top-level class in the same file, matching the existing pattern used by the other Spring Boot Jackson test. This should avoid JUnit native test-class registration traversing Spring’s `KotlinDelegate` nested class while preserving coverage for the active runtime hints dynamic-access call site.
[assistant-event] text_end
